  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Quantity Surveyor",
  "description": "<h2><strong>Quantity Surveyor (Aluminium & Façade Works)</strong></h2><h3><strong>Job Scope / Responsibilities</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Prepare <strong>cost estimates, budgets, and Bills of Quantities (BQ)</strong> for aluminium, glazing, façade, curtain wall, windows and doors works.</p></li><li><p>Carry out <strong>tender pricing</strong>, cost comparison, and value engineering for aluminium systems, profiles, glass, accessories, and related materials.</p></li><li><p>Source and obtain <strong>quotations from suppliers, fabricators, and subcontractors</strong>, including overseas suppliers where applicable.</p></li><li><p>Prepare and evaluate <strong>subcontractor and supplier agreements</strong>, ensuring compliance with project specifications and contract requirements.</p></li><li><p>Monitor <strong>project costs</strong>, track variations, and manage cost control throughout the project lifecycle.</p></li><li><p>Prepare <strong>progress claims, variation orders (VO), final accounts</strong>, and assist in settlement with main contractors or clients.</p></li><li><p>Coordinate with <strong>Project Managers, Engineers, Designers, and Production Teams</strong> to ensure costing aligns with drawings, shop drawings, and site conditions.</p></li><li><p>Review and verify <strong>material take-offs</strong> based on architectural and shop drawings.</p></li><li><p>Assist in <strong>procurement planning</strong>, delivery schedules, and cost forecasting.</p></li><li><p>Support contract administration including <strong>payment certifications, claims documentation, and cost reports</strong>.</p></li><li><p>Maintain proper documentation for <strong>cost records, contracts, and variations</strong>.</p></li></ul><h3><strong>Requirements</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Diploma / Degree in <strong>Quantity Surveying, Construction Management, or related field</strong>.</p></li><li><p>Experience in <strong>aluminium, façade, glazing, or metal works</strong> will be an advantage.</p></li><li><p>Familiar with <strong>aluminium systems, glass specifications, accessories, and installation methods</strong>.</p></li><li><p>Able to read and interpret <strong>architectural, structural, and shop drawings</strong>.</p></li><li><p>Proficient in <strong>Excel</strong>; experience with QS software is a plus.</p></li><li><p>Good communication and negotiation skills.</p></li><li><p>Detail-oriented, responsible, and able to work independently.</p></li></ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 5,
